+- Runtime conditions: shadow-drift detection can emit operational events; compatibility routes like `/sync` still exist; tasks outside the active teaching scope may be ignored
+- Persistence or config coupling: in repo mode the same repositories fall back to local storage; in live mode the same actions flow through API-backed runtime routes and queued proof refresh work
+- Hidden coupling sources: the same edit can be local-only or backend-persisted depending on repository mode; proof refresh queueing is contingent on a background consumer that is not directly visible in the UI
+- Failure mode: shadow drift can leave local and backend state out of sync; proof refresh can be queued but not yet executed; live parity can lag after curriculum or policy edits
+- Drift risk: high
+- Evidence: `src/repositories.ts:353-500, 552-587, 697-823, 868-879`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/academic-runtime-routes.ts:104-863, 1055-1056`, `src/system-admin-live-app.tsx:3906-4410, 4658-4665, 4072-4116, 4135-4246`, `air-mentor-api/src/modules/admin-proof-sandbox.ts:1-240`
+- Notes: unresolved ambiguity - the background worker or cron consumer that completes queued proof-refresh jobs was not traced in this pass
+
